Interface SearchParams

Parameters for finding DataObjects with Data.searchDataObjects.

These parameters configure the way that Data.searchDataObjects performs its depth-first search to find our DataObjects.

See Data for usage examples.

Optional includeStart

includeStart: boolean
  • Defined in webviewer/src/viewer/data/SearchParams.ts:50

Indicates whether to include the SearchParams.startObjectId or SearchParams.startObject in search results.

Default is true.

Optional resultCallback

resultCallback: (dataObject: DataObject) => boolean
  • Defined in webviewer/src/viewer/data/SearchParams.ts:101

Type declaration

    • (dataObject: DataObject): boolean

    • Collects the search results via a callback that's executed on each matching DataObject.

      This is mutually exclusive with SearchParams.resultObjects and SearchParams.resultObjectIds.

      Parameters

      • dataObject: DataObject

      Returns boolean
